text.section:
A special nonbeverage alcohol license shall authorize the holder to purchase alcohol for nonbeverage purposes only from the holder of a distiller's license, wholesaler's license, or distributor's license and possess alcohol for use in the manufacture and sale of any of the following products, when they are unfit for beverage purposes:
Denatured alcohol produced, and sold pursuant to Acts of Congress and regulations promulgated thereunder;
Patent, proprietary, medicinal, pharmaceutical, antiseptic, and toilet preparations;
Flavoring extracts, syrups, and food products; and
Scientific, chemical, mechanical, and industrial products.
